      "side": 1,
      "message": "I looked at Jgit implementation to see what it does when `parseCommit` is called on an annotated `tag` and it does the following:\n\n```\n\tpublic RevCommit parseCommit(AnyObjectId id) throws MissingObjectException,\n\t\t\tIncorrectObjectTypeException, IOException {\n\t\tRevObject c \u003d peel(parseAny(id));\n\t\tif (!(c instanceof RevCommit))\n\t\t\tthrow new IncorrectObjectTypeException(id.toObjectId(),\n\t\t\t\t\tConstants.TYPE_COMMIT);\n\t\treturn (RevCommit) c;\n\t}\n```\n\nSee how it `peels()` the annotated tag with `RevObject c \u003d peel(parseAny(id));`, which loops until a non-tag is found:\n\n```\n\tpublic RevObject peel(RevObject obj)\n\t\t\tthrows MissingObjectException, IOException {\n\t\twhile (obj instanceof RevTag) {\n\t\t\tparseHeaders(obj);\n\t\t\tobj \u003d ((RevTag) obj).getObject();\n\t\t}\n\t\tparseHeaders(obj);\n\t\treturn obj;\n\t}\n```\n\nThis means that here, we are logging metadata for the **peeled commit**, not for the annotated tag. I would have expected this to be handled via `walk.parseTag()`, have you considered that?\n\n```\ncase OBJ_TAG:\n   RevTag revTag \u003d walk.parseTag(newRefValue);\n   committer \u003d CommonConverters.toGitPerson(revTag.getTaggerIdent());\n   commitMessage \u003d revTag.getShortMessage();\n   break;\n```",
